{"id": "1470727907449114658", "channel_id": "1436913827571695898", "type": 19, "author_id": "1372028651175936080", "author_name": "Morimens", "author_bot": true, "content": "**Hameln (Hamelin)** – Lower Saxony, Germany  \n*Population (2023):* **≈ 57,900**  \n\n**Key points**\n\n- **Location:** On the Weser River, about 50 km southwest of Hanover.  \n- **History:** Chartered around 1200; former member of the Hanseatic League.  \n- **Economy:** Electrical products, textiles, chemicals, machinery, food processing, and a notable tourism sector.  \n- **Famous for:** The **Pied Piper of Hameln** legend (1284) – a major tourist draw with the Ratcatcher’s House, the Wedding House, and medieval half‑timbered architecture.  \n- **Transport:** Rail junction and river port; good road links to the rest of Germany.  \n\n*Quick tip:* If you visit, check out the **Pied Piper Museum** and the **Weser Renaissance** buildings in the old town.", "timestamp": "2026-02-10T10:27:37.939000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["694573382380945529"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1470727885613699134", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1470727997978837125", "channel_id": "1436913827571695898", "type": 0, "author_id": "694573382380945529", "author_name": "craux.", "author_bot": false, "content": "<@1372028651175936080> info about hameln from morimens", "timestamp": "2026-02-10T10:27:59.523000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["1372028651175936080"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
{"id": "1470728024004759680", "channel_id": "1436913827571695898", "type": 19, "author_id": "1372028651175936080", "author_name": "Morimens", "author_bot": true, "content": "**Hameln – Morimens**\n\n- **Rarity / Role:** SSR Assist (Chaos faction)  \n- **Base Stats @ Lvl 60**  \n  - CON: 120 (+1.5)  \n  - ATK: 124 (+1.55)  \n  - DEF: 116 (+1.45)  \n  - Crit Rate: 9.8 % (+0.8 %)  \n  - Crit DMG: 50 %  \n  - Keyflare Regen: 29.4 (+2.4)  \n\n- **Core Passives**  \n  - **Mind Concerto:** *Strike* / *Defend* grant temporary STR = 10 % ATK (doubles if a “Melody” triggers).  \n  - **Oneiric Waltz:** *Rondino* reduces its Arithmetica cost by 2.  \n  - **Moonlit Rhapsphere:** Triggering a “Melody” or playing **[Symphony of Harmony]** gives +1 % Crit Rate & Crit DMG.  \n\n- **Key Cards**  \n  - **Laudable Masterpiece** – Grants Aliemus (25/30/35/40/45/50). *Rouse*: adds **[Symphony of Harmony]** at turn start (retain).  \n  - **Symphony of Harmony** – Choose **Ascending Scale** (+2 cost, double effect) or **Descending Scale** (‑2 cost). (Exhaust, retain).  \n  - **Strike** – Deals 10/12/14/16/18/20 % ATK dmg, gives 5/6/7/8/9/10 Aliemus.  \n  - **Defend** – Grants 10/12/14/16/18/20 % DEF shield.  \n\n- **Typical Playstyle**  \n  - Use **Laudable Masterpiece** to seed **Symphony of Harmony**, then manipulate Arithmetica costs with the scale choices.  \n  - Leverage the temporary STR boost for burst damage or survivability, especially when “Melody” effects trigger.  \n\n- **Wheels (suggested)**  \n  - **Signature Wheel** – Hameln’s own wheel (usually best synergy).  \n  - **Chaos Wheel** – Good all‑round alternative for extra crit/regen.  \n  - **Support Wheel** – If you need more shield or Aliemus generation.  \n\n*TL;DR*: Hameln is a Chaos‑assist SSR that excels at cost‑control and temporary STR buffs via “Melody” triggers. Pair with his signature wheel or a Chaos‑type wheel for optimal performance.", "timestamp": "2026-02-10T10:28:05.728000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["694573382380945529"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1470727997978837125", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
